names of your parents, places and dates of their 
birth and death, the place where you were born and

00:08.005 --> 00:21.683
the date of your birth, and the schools you 
attended before you came to Texas A&M. My father

00:23.105 --> 00:33.598
was born in Georgia in 1856, and It was in a rural 
community.

00:40.437 --> 00:57.207
I don't know of any large town there, but it was in 
the area to the northeast of Atlanta somewhere

00:40.437 --> 00:57.207
because I recall hearing

00:40.437 --> 00:57.207
him talk, speak of

00:59.903 --> 01:11.381
Being on the edge of Sherman's march to the sea, he 
saw and heard some of the soldiers

00:59.903 --> 01:11.381
coming and going during that time. And

01:12.422 --> 01:23.920
his name was H.C.

01:12.422 --> 01:23.920
Harrison C. Kerbo.

01:25.587 --> 01:45.327
Several of the, he, his father and

01:25.587 --> 01:45.327
several families of the Curbos came to northeast 
Texas along about 1867

01:25.587 --> 01:45.327
and settled in Red River County. Later on, they 
moved to, some of them moved over into Delta

01:46.348 --> 01:54.936
County, close to Cooper, Texas.

