born before the Civil War. She was born in 1860 in

02:08.528 --> 02:15.918
Octobahaw County, Mississippi.

02:18.942 --> 02:23.488
And her family also came to Texas long about that 
time and settled in the area somewhere around

02:24.599 --> 02:31.087
where Sherman now is, whatever county that might 
be. And later they also moved to Delta County. In

02:37.375 --> 02:52.193
1900,

02:37.375 --> 02:52.193
my father sold out his business in Delta County and 
moved to West Texas in Fisher County.

02:53.624 --> 03:14.594
raised

02:53.624 --> 03:14.594
some livestock and did a little farming and had a 
general merchandise country store and post

02:53.624 --> 03:14.594
office about 20 miles west of Stamford and 20 miles 
from Robie. It was quite an isolated country,

03:14.634 --> 03:19.160
territory in those days. Then in 1905, The family 
moved to Clarendon, Texas when I was about 10 years

03:23.122 --> 03:29.412
old. And I went through grade high school in 
Clarendon, Texas, and then went from there to

03:30.534 --> 03:42.975
Texas A&M. How did you make the move first to the 
vicinity of Stanford? I beg your pardon? how how

03:49.683 --> 04:17.142
was the move made from east texas to stamford it was 
made by uh it was made by a train with a chartered car

03:49.683 --> 04:17.142
to carry livestock and household goods and so on 
and then by wagon to be placed west of stamford over

03:49.683 --> 04:17.142
in fisher county then in the move from

04:19.501 --> 04:32.138
Fisher County to Clarendon was made in with a wagon 
and Surrey and then also a chartered car to carry

04:19.501 --> 04:32.138
household goods and so on. We went through in a 
wagon and Surrey covered wagon. Must have been

04:40.288 --> 04:43.453
quite an experience for a ten-year-old boy. Well 
yes, however I had another experience Prior to

04:49.083 --> 05:18.043
that, when we were living in Fisher County, and I 
was about seven, I guess, years old, along about

04:49.083 --> 05:18.043
1902, I suppose it was, our family, the younger 
children in our family and two other families with

04:49.083 --> 05:18.043
children, decided to have a vacation trip up 
across the plains, wagon, covered wagon trip. And

05:19.255 --> 05:22.398
we did, and that was quite an experience. And I 
remember Lubbock particularly because I never

05:22.538 --> 05:34.270
had seen so many windmills in one place in all my 
life as they were here. And I recall watering our

05:35.091 --> 05:49.245
livestock, horses, going with my father to water 
those at a stock trough. I believe by the

05:49.748 --> 05:54.093
courthouse, the old courthouse, wherever that 
was. It was in Lubbock? Here in Lubbock. We camped

05:56.757 --> 06:03.084
somewhere off outside the city. By today's 
standards, one would hardly think of a trek across

06:03.104 --> 06:08.391
the plains by wagon as a vacation. No, I guess not. 
