21:21.653 --> 21:23.375
I don't remember that they did. I don't believe so. 
I believe at one point there were rules that

21:24.657 --> 21:28.682
forbade the cards on campus. I think so. I think so. 
Also cigarettes. How about cigars and chewing

21:32.868 --> 21:34.770
tobacco? Cigars, I believe, were not

21:36.893 --> 21:42.460
allowed. Chewing tobacco was not ruled out 
because I recall I did a little cartooning while I

21:43.161 --> 21:51.492
was there. for the battalion, and I made a strip 
like mutton, Jeff,

21:52.265 --> 22:12.266
and I believe one of them asked the other for a 
cigarette, and he didn't have any cigarettes, but

21:52.265 --> 22:12.266
he had some Star Navy, and it was cheaper anyway. 
And that was a popular brand at the time? Star Navy

22:15.409 --> 22:18.272
tobacco, oh yes, it was very popular. But 
actually, there was some cigarette smoking going

22:19.315 --> 22:26.242
on, although not too many boys. Was that a serious 
punishable offense if you were caught? Yes, it

22:30.666 --> 22:35.131
was, but I don't recall what the amount of 
punishment was. As a matter of fact, you got, I

22:36.092 --> 22:42.298
believe they call it rams. You got rammed for lots 
of things. I spent some time on the campus working

22:50.281 --> 22:56.127
around on the grounds, working off demerits. So 
you would work off your demerits that way rather

22:57.088 --> 23:01.693
than marching in the bullring or something? I 
never did have to march. I don't, I believe that

23:04.255 --> 23:06.498
