Did the upperclassmen have any privileges that 
were not accorded to the freshmen? Oh, yes, but I

25:41.225 --> 25:43.829
don't recall what they were. Yes, sure, the 
upperclassmen had lots of privileges that the

25:44.229 --> 25:52.662
freshmen didn't have. I presume that ability of 
doing a little hazing was one. Oh, yes, yes.

25:59.391 --> 26:10.067
However, hazing was never a real problem because I 
noticed that the

25:59.391 --> 26:10.067
upperclassmen didn't haze freshmen whom they 
didn't like personally. And of course, the

26:16.515 --> 26:36.760
freshmen, we,

26:16.515 --> 26:36.760
at least I did, and I guess some of the others did, we 
